If no comparison is possible as, e.g., a new risk category was introduced, the trend is shown as (∅). ","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"To calculate the trend, the system calculates a rating number per question/topic/risk category per year, and calculates the difference to the former years. This is achieved by subtracting the previous year's rating number from the current year's rating number.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"For example, if the rating number of Topic No.1 in 2024 is 2 (Partially) and in 2023 is 4 (Fully) then the comparison will be shown as 2 half-down arrows (↘↘) in Red. Historical Data","textStyle":{"fontWeight":"bold","fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"The digitized solution of managing PC Checks in GRC was introduced in 2024. The historical PC Checks from 2018 to 2023 were entered into GRC as well - but the results displayed for the former years can differ from what was reported in the former years. This has the following reasons:","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"1.","textStyle":{"color":"#000000"}},{"value":" GRC only allows to select current OE-data. So it was not possible to e.g. add a PC Check with \"OE=AE\"(an OE of a year <2024) but only as \"OE=ME\" or \"OE=BST\" (depending on which current OE fits best). When entering the PC Checks, C/PCO mapped the PC Checks to the OE, where the assessed project would now reside. This means:","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt","color":"#000000"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"The OE name for historical data is always the OE name which was available in 2024.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt","color":"#000000"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"The accumulation is according to the organization of 2024, not the one of the former years.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt","color":"#000000"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Historical PC Checks for Bosch Packaging are not shown in GRC, as the OE is not part of the Bosch group anymore.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt","color":"#000000"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"2."},{"value":" In 2018 and 2019 the annual report was calculated according to different formulas. In the Dashboard we use the calculation formula which is valid since 2020 for all years.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"12pt"}}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"3. "},{"value":"In 2018 the rating for PC Checks was only \"fully(green)\", \"partially (yellow)\", \"partially(red)\" and \"N/A(grey)\".
